### Notepad 3: `supabase-query-patterns`
```
Content to store:

Standard Supabase query patterns for Rocket.new projects:

// Single row (may not exist)
const { data } = await supabase.from('table').select('*').eq('id', id).maybeSingle()

// Single row (guaranteed exists — use only when certain)
const { data } = await supabase.from('table').select('*').eq('id', id).single()

// List with user filter
const { data } = await supabase.from('table').select('*')
  .eq('user_id', user.id).order('created_at', { ascending: false })

// With join
const { data } = await supabase.from('posts')
  .select('*, profiles(display_name, avatar_url)')
  .eq('user_id', user.id)

// Parallel queries (always use Promise.all for multiple queries)
const [profileRes, postsRes] = await Promise.all([
  supabase.from('profiles').select('*').eq('id', user.id).single(),
  supabase.from('posts').select('*').eq('user_id', user.id)
])

// Upsert
const { data } = await supabase.from('table').upsert({ id, ...data }).select()
```

**Usage**: `@supabase-query-patterns then write the data fetching for the dashboard page`

